# Elayne Trakand · Daughter-Heir of Andor, the Green

Elayne Trakand is the Daughter-Heir of Andor, fighting to claim the Lion Throne left empty by her murdered mother, and later reaching for the throne of Cairhien as well. Proud, clever, and politically fearless, she pursues her birthright with a will that bends courts and councils to her purpose. Her struggle is one of crowns and claims — the contest for who shall sit and rule, fought in the open arena of worldly power.

A strong channeler of the Green Ajah, she is also a gifted maker of ter'angreal, shaping objects of the One Power with a craftsman's hand. Her place in the saga joins the work of the White Tower to the business of thrones, so that what she wields in the Power serves what she means to hold in the world.

She is bound to Rand in love alongside Min and Aviendha, and she carries his heirs — a thread that ties the line of Andor to the Dragon himself. Birgitte is her Warder, sworn at her side through the dangers her ambitions invite.

Her emergence is natural, for Elayne is one of the world's embodied powers — a woman of throne and lineage, of court and crown. Though she channels and makes, her essence belongs to the worldly order of queens and nations, and so the natural nature fits her best.
